  "text": "To demonstrate that the decreased radioprotective capacity of the S/G2/M cells was itself not responsible for the decrease in donor-derived long-term reconstitution capacity of S/G2/M cells, we employed a competitive repopulation assay [CITATION_1] . Lethally irradiated recipient mice were injected with 2 x 1@ syngeneic bone marrow cells and either 100 G0/GI or 100 S/G2/M cells. This dose of syngeneic bone marrow provides radioprotection to the recipient mice while permitting the G0/G1 and the S/G2/M cell subsets to undergo lineage specific differentiation. Recipient mice were analyzed 9 mo postinjection. When 100 G0/G1",
